A lot of people suffers with snoring and if you don't, you probably know someone who does. Snoring happens when air flows through your throat when you breathe in your sleep. This causes the relaxed tissues in your throat to vibrate and cause harsh, irritating snoring sounds. Snoring can disrupt you or your loved one's sleep and sometimes it might even be a sign of a serious health condition like obstructive sleep apnea (blocked airways), obesityan issue with the structure of your mouth, nose, or throat or sleep deprivation. It is important to seek a doctor's advice in order to get the medical diagnosis or treatment. These 3 items might help you with snoring: 1. Nasal Dilators  2. Snoring Chin Strap  3. Anti Snoring Nose Clips 